task.summary: Default task
Corrected a problem in RespondFragment's recyclerView when setting the data for Freeform questions (it used the wrong way to figure out the position).
- Initial commit for RecyclerAdapterBase.java - Replaced the Adapter in RespondFragment.java with the new class.
QuestionnaireFragment changed so that its adapter now uses the RecyclerAdapterBase instead of reinventing the wheel.
Localized most of the onBindViewHolder method to make overriding easier.
- Refactoring - First commit for RankDialogFragment.java - Many changes so that the Rank dialog returns data.
- First commit for RankCardViewHolder.java and rank_card.xml. - Now RecyclerView display of CardViews in the RankDialogFragment display.
Now touch drags work for the RecyclerView.
Corrected some weirdness in the QuestionRank class.
initial commit
Modified for the new Activity (as a dialog).
Changed minimum sdk to 21 (lollipop).
Added modification that prevents the RankDialogActivity from recognizing clicks outside its borders.

Many changes--converting from using an AlertDialog to using an Activity dressed up as a dialog. This greatly simplifies and encapsulates the data exchange (no need for an interface in MainActivity and the Fragment can communicate directly with the new Activity).
Removed unused class. See previous commit.
RecyclerView in the RankActivity now displays (but doesn't yet move).
Greatly simplified the QuestionRank class.
Finally! The RespondFragment correctly displays modified rank data from the RankDialogActivity.
Layout improvements.
- Updated gradle - RankActivity now sends data back to the caller properly. - RespondFragment updates with RankActivity data - Beginning to make FAB in RespondFragment functional.

- FAB now has a lock on it so it fires at most every two seconds. This hack fixes a problem with multiple clicks on the FAB causing multiple dialogs (which would cause multiple data streams to be sent). - The FAB's dialog now won't cancel when it's clicked outside the window. User MUST click cancel to cancel.
- First Commit for CreateQuestionDialogActivity.java and question_dialog.xml. - Basic UI functionality working for this new Activity/Dialog.
Played with FAB. Figured out how to correctly change its background color.
- Lots of data changes, mostly adding functionality to the four Question sub-classes in preparation for sending data back from the CreateQuestionDialogActivity.
- Some data is now being passed from the CreateQuestionDialogActivity to the QuestionFragment (just the FreeForm data). - Added response optional functionality to the Freeform question type.
initial checkin. These are new layout files for creating questions.
A huge checkin! But still working on the making the questionnaire fully functional. This is a good place to make a bookmark.
Another huge check-in. Still working on creating the questionnaire. More to do, but this compiles and runs with lots of the new changes.
Another huge check-in. Still working on creating the questionnaire. More to do, but this compiles and runs with lots of the new changes.
Minor changes, trying to get the layout to look professional.
Still more changes dealing with making an actual checkbox editor. Mostly moving away from using the BaseQuestionView in favor of the more specific CheckboxQuestionView. Still lots to go.
Small addition that forces the recyclerview to scroll to the end when an item is added.
Removed unused code (was designed for testing).
Moving from using BaseQuestionView. CheckboxQuestionView is just as functional now.
Managed to figure out some of the theme issues. The Checkbox Question activities are now corrected.
Cleaned up an unnecessary todo comment.
CreateQuestionCheckboxDialogActivity now properly returning its recyclerview data. And that data is properly displayed (mostly) in QuestionnaireFragment.
Got the CreateRadioButtonActivity and subordinate classes working.
Now the ranking seems to be working in the Questionnaire. At least minimally.
Freeform question creator is now nominally functional.
- Removed unused fragment class. - QuestionnaireFragment now maintains its data correctly.
A little cleaning up.
RespondFragment now disables after the user submits their response.
Snackbar now informs the user that they sent out results.
RespondFragment now remembers its state, so you can swipe to other aspects without changing this at all.
Added a send FAB for the Questionnaire.
Re-vamped the RecyclerView in the QuestionnaireFragment. It now displays using the new custom Views. Still requires some tweaks, but this change should make life a lot easier in the long run.

- Added a change to manifest to force EditTexts to pan so we can see them if the soft keyboard covers that part of the screen. - Freeform questions are in create mode when displayed in QuestionnaireFragment.
- Modifications so the Questionnaire is more usable. - CheckboxQuestionView now handles the two modes (responding & creating) better.
Still fine-tuning the CheckboxQuestionView. Now it visually changes better when switching between the Editable and Respondable states. Whew, that was a lot of work!
